result.execSummary:
On one or more charges, the deferred prosecution or sentencing agreement(s) on this case were fulfilled, and the charge(s) were dismissed.

The defendant Michelle Ann Driscoll was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

CO: Cameron, RPR: Deiss , Clerk: Liddle ADA:  Kevin H. Gehler   DF ATTY:  Shirlene Renee Perrin   DF:  Michelle Ann Driscoll appeared. Case called at 1:18 p.m. Atty Perrin addressing Motion to Suppress that was filed by Atty Morse. Illegal search by probation agent. ADA Gehler is prepared to address that if that is the issue. S/T Probation Agent Cassandra Moll. ADA Gehler directs.  Agent Moll identifies defendant in the courtroom. Asked for River Falls PD to assist in a home search if UA was dirty. Agent Moll and Officer Posel from River Falls P.D. went with defendant to get UA. No valid UA was obtained. Officer Sather gathered evidence and taking notes on items that were found on home search. Atty Perrin redirects Agent Moll. No further questions by either party. Agent Moll excused at 1:31 p.m. S/T Srgnt Sather with the River Falls Police Department. ADA Gehler directs. By the request of Agent Moll, Officer Sather collected and docketed evidence that was found on the home search. Srgnt Sather excused at 1:35 p.m.  S/T Officer Knutson with the River Falls Police Department. Atty Perrin directs. Officer Knutson identifies defendant in the courtroom. Officer Knutson was asked by Agent Moll to take defendant into custody for PO Hold. Officer Knutson excused at 1:39 p.m. No further testimony. Atty Perrin makes statement. ADA Gehler makes arguement that probation has right to search if suspected use. Atty Perrin would like to submit a written arguement. Court finds officers testimony and agents testimony is credible. Reasonable grounds for search with 3 failed UA's. Atty Perrin makes statement. Court file a Motion for Reconsideration to Atty Perrin. ADA Gehler gives arguement. Case adjourned at 1:49 p.m. hml  Pre-trial conference scheduled for January 22, 2015 at 01:00 pm.
